        <page n="01" image="va.au.ss.1859.12.27.01">
            <div type="l">
                <column>6</column>
                <head/>
                <origin/>
                <excerpt>"In these days of military activity, it may be a matter of curiosity to
                    recall to mind the names of those who only a few years ago were ready to respond
                    to the call of their country. How few of them yet remain among us; yet we see
                    their sons now motivated by the same spirit--worthy sons of worthy sires. I may
                    yet hunt you up other documents of this sort though more ancient."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>J. M. McC.</trailer>
                <commentary/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Roster of 93rd Virginia, upon their mustering out in 1814. Indication of
                    Augusta's patriotism then and now.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="l">
                <column>7</column>
                <head>For the Spectator</head>
                <origin/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <commentary/>
                <names/>
                <summary>"Justice," who wrote a letter to the paper on August 23 complaining about
                    faulty tax collection is writing again. He blamed the commissioners originally
                    but now sees that the problems are not their fault. Bottom of letter is
                    obscured.</summary>
            </div>
            <pageNote>Letter in col. 5 from Daniel Boone and others. Bottom right corner is too dark
                to read.</pageNote>
        </page>
